Though presently still an experimental feature, you can also specify that tests should be executed [in parallel](https://junit.org/junit5/docs/current/user-guide/#writing-tests-parallel-execution), by setting the `junit.jupiter.execution.parallel.enabled` to true as part of your [JUnit 5 configuration settings](https://junit.org/junit5/docs/current/user-guide/#running-tests-config-params).

Your code would then look as follows:

```
@Execution(CONCURRENT)
class GoogleSearchTest {

  import ...

  @RepeatedTest(10)
  public void searchInGoogle() {
    ...
  }
}
```

